Random Quote Generator:

Create a webpage that displays a new random quote each time a button is clicked.
Store quotes in an array and use JavaScript to randomly select and display one.
Interactive Dice Roller:

Build a dice rolling simulator where users can click a button to roll a six-sided die and display the result.
Interactive Calculator (Basic):

Design a calculator interface with HTML buttons for digits and basic operations (addition, subtraction, multiplication, division).
Implement JavaScript to perform calculations based on user input.
Color Guessing Game:

Create a game where the user has to guess the RGB color value shown on the screen.
Provide feedback on whether the guessed color is correct or not.
Simple To-Do List with Local Storage:

Develop a to-do list where users can add, delete, and mark tasks as completed.
Use local storage to persist tasks even after refreshing the page.
Interactive Image Gallery:

Build a gallery of images where users can click on thumbnails to display a larger version in a modal or lightbox.
Form Autofill with JSON Data:

Create a form that autofills fields (e.g., name, email) based on JSON data when a button is clicked.
Use JavaScript to fetch and parse JSON data.
Countdown Timer with Alarm:

Develop a countdown timer that allows users to set a specific time and receive an alert or play a sound when the countdown reaches zero.
Currency Converter:

Design a simple currency converter where users can enter an amount in one currency and convert it to another using live exchange rates fetched from an API.
Tic-Tac-Toe Game:

Implement a two-player Tic-Tac-Toe game where users can click on squares to place X's and O's.
Include logic to determine the winner or if the game ends in a draw.
